And thus there are distinct and appropriate spheres of action of God, the Legislator, and the J udge. God delivers general precepts3 the Legislator determines them to special kinds of persons and actions3 the Judge applies them effectively to special cases of persons and actions.

And thus if the Legislator makes a Law contrary to the precepts of God, it is an unrighteous Law: if the Judge pronounce a sentence contrary to the Law of the Prince, it is an unrighteous sentence.
